+# Prior-Art Overlap Collapses The Live Menu To One Pressure-Hessian Family With No Novelty Clearance
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` with `INFERRED` branch consequence
+
+After the Step-009 endpoint freeze, the Step-010 prior-art screen does not
+leave a broad family menu alive. On the local record, the only serious
+survivor is one pressure-Hessian / strain-defect family attached to the frozen
+far-field pairing `I_p^far`.
+
+The same screen also collapses several nearby labels:
+
+- `harmonic-moment cancellation` is not a second family; it survives only as a
+  mechanism subquestion inside that same pressure-side family;
+- `alignment`, `eigenframe`, `restricted-Euler`, and
+  `conditional-regularity` language function here as prior-art comparators or
+  packaging aliases, not as independent Step-10 survivors;
+- and `full stretching control` remains descriptive bottleneck rhetoric on this
+  record unless it acquires an exact cash-out on the frozen far-field ledger.
+
+The operational verdict is narrower still. Even the remaining
+pressure-Hessian-centered family has not yet cleared novelty. It stays alive
+only as one overlap-screened candidate family that must still show
+packaging-independent coefficient shrinkage on the same full pairing, rather
+than a reformulation of known pressure-Hessian or restricted-Euler-adjacent
+language.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-010-exploration-001-prior-art-overlap-screen.md`
